{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17612163","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17612163"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T14:18:34+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T14:18:34+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16264"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16264","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16264"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.78,0.06,0.09,0.06,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8955"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65149"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8955","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8955"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16264"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50585"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5113"},{"type":"tags","id":"5372"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21299"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21302"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65149","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/65149"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAgeing is associated with various physiological changes that affect nutrient requirements and metabolism.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following nutrients has increased recommended daily intake requirements with advancing age?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Vitamin D","Vitamin C","Iron","Zinc","Selenium"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe recommended daily intake of \u003Cstrong\u003Evitamin D\u003C/strong\u003E increases with age due to several factors:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EReduced capacity of skin to synthesize vitamin D from sunlight exposure\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDecreased intestinal absorption of vitamin D\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EReduced outdoor activity and sun exposure\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDecreased renal conversion of vitamin D to its active form (calcitriol).\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHigher risk of osteoporosis and fractures, making vitamin D crucial for maintaining bone health and calcium metabolism.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options do not typically require increased intake with age:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVitamin C\u003C/strong\u003E requirements remain relatively stable throughout adult life.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIron\u003C/strong\u003E requirements actually decrease in post-menopausal women because they no longer lose iron through menstruation. In men, the requirement remains unchanged with age.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EZinc\u003C/strong\u003E requirements remain constant throughout adulthood.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESelenium\u003C/strong\u003E requirements do not change significantly with age.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe recommended daily intake of vitamin D for adults over 70 years is higher than for younger adults, reflecting these age-related changes in vitamin D metabolism and increased risk of deficiency.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Vitamin D requirements increase with age due to reduced skin synthesis and decreased intestinal absorption.","Older adults have higher risk of vitamin D deficiency due to reduced sun exposure and impaired vitamin D metabolism.","Adequate vitamin D is crucial for maintaining bone health and preventing osteoporosis in older adults."],"references":["Giustina A, Bouillon R, Dawson-Hughes B, Ebeling PR, Lazaretti-Castro M, Lips P, Marcocci C, Bilezikian JP. Vitamin D in the older population: a consensus statement. Endocrine. 2023 Jan;79(1):31-44. doi: 10.1007/s12020-022-03208-3. Epub 2022 Oct 26. PMID: 36287374; PMCID: PMC9607753.","Gallagher JC. Vitamin D and aging. Endocrinol Metab Clin North Am. 2013 Jun;42(2):319-32. doi: 10.1016/j.ecl.2013.02.004. Epub 2013 Apr 9. PMID: 23702404; PMCID: PMC3782116.","Meehan M, Penckofer S. The Role of Vitamin D in the Aging Adult. J Aging Gerontol. 2014 Dec;2(2):60-71. doi: 10.12974/2309-6128.2014.02.02.1. PMID: 25893188; PMCID: PMC4399494."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50585"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16264"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50585","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/50585"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-25T16:28:18+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-25T16:28:59+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8955"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65149"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-cli